<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-18T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="893" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d893">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.931/5–1849: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-18T17:00:00+08:00">May 18,
                                    1949—5 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1059. AMilAt and EmbOff today called at Aliens Affairs Office to present
                            written protest (Deptel 576, May 12). Document was returned with
                            statement military authorities now arranging interview in near future
                            with Embassy officer concerning incident. From this development it
                            appears may soon be possible present both oral and written protest
                            direct to military authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>